  "body": "Fee recipient overwritten by the beacon node. \r\n\r\nOur setup has produced a block with an incorrect fee recipient:https://beaconcha.in/slot/4700831 it used beacon fee recipient instead of  validator client  fee recipient\r\n\r\nWe have a 3-layer configuration with the validator client, the Beacon node and the execution client running separately.\r\n\r\n```\r\nValidator set up - version: Lighthouse/v3.1.0-aa022f4\r\n--graffiti \"Block by Stakely Lido02\"\r\n--suggested-fee-recipient 0x388C818CA8B9251b393131C08a736A67ccB19297\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nBeacon set up -  version: Lighthouse/v3.1.0-aa022f4\r\n--graffiti \"Block by Stakely.io - lh01\"\r\n--suggested-fee-recipient 0x7188D41ea11aBf3e95040ba1823E861A62644AC2\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n`Execution Client - version Geth Version: 1.10.23-stable\r\n`\r\nThe block should be produced with Validator Client suggested-fee-recipient value. \r\n\r\nWe have removed the suggested-fee-recipient from the beacon node and it works. Setting the suggested-fee-recipient of the Validator client and the Beacon node to the same value also works. \r\n",
